					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Before working on the arpeggio enhancements, I wanted to get some changes out into a tagged release for those who don't follow me on GitHub.<br /><br />0.05wip6 (2017-06)<br /><br /><ul><li>Patterns can change channel volume in 25% steps</li><li>Rest in attack track no longer corrupts pulse 1 arpeggio</li><li>pentlyconfig.inc: Change engine's code and data segment; disable pulse channel effect pooling and volume comparison; change initial $4011 value</li><li>Optionally enable sound effects in NSF</li><li>pentlyas.py: Improved diagnostics emitted by play command. Shows song name; emits one for playing pattern too low.</li><li>pentlyas.py: Command line option to change output segment</li><li>pentlyas.py: Clamp vibrato depth to in-range values</li><li>pentlyas.py: Ignore loops in volume envelopes, presumably pasted from FamiTracker</li><li>NSF header gets load address from linker configuration</li><li>Document use of equal temperament</li><li>Add &quot;Sticks&quot; sample song</li></ul></div>

					
						<br clear="all" /><br />

