				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Pently 0.05wip7 has three key improvements: portamento, slow arpeggio, and richer ways to express arpeggio.<br /><br /><ul><li>Change to zlib license, which preserves the spirit of the original license but is recognizable by GitHub</li><li>Add portamento, the single most requested feature</li><li>paldetect: Interleave with vwait so as not to depend on NMI handler</li><li>pentlyas.py: Add 8 predefined chord names (M, maj7, dom7, aug, m, m7, dim, dim7)</li><li>pentlyas.py: Score can define new chord names</li><li>pentlyas.py: Add single-note arpeggio syntax similar to LilyPond chord mode (thanks to retrodpc for testing)</li><li>pentlyas.py: Option to name chord by its top note instead of bottom</li><li>pentlyas.py: First and second inversions of chords</li><li>Arpeggio can be set to slow or fast (requested by w7n)</li><li>Add &quot;Arpeggio Waltz&quot; song demonstrating new features</li><li>Document that object names follow identifier rules</li><li>makefile: Launch Python tools with py.exe on Windows</li></ul></div>

					
						<br clear="all" /><br />

